<br>
Now that is scary.<br>
<br>
So, using your smoker example...you assume that the woman smoking has no self-control, will die of cancer, and obviously must hate herself...otherwise why would she smoke? <br>
Can you apply that to a person at a bar? They're all alcoholics, looking for a cheap hook-up, hating their life so they must drown themselves in booze?<br>
What about a person wearing a tie? Must be some money-hungry corporate shlub?<br>
A vietnam vet? Must be a baby-killer?<br>
<br>
There are things, Krazak, that just *are*. Not everything has some hidden meaning. I like chocolate ice cream. That doesn't mean I hate my father, or that it's just that time of the month. It just means that I like chocolate ice cream. Stop taking Freud so seriously...along with Psych 101...sheesh.<br>
<br>
I smoke. One ciggy per week, on Saturday morning. And you can make whatever shallow generalization you want about me, lol. <br>
<br>
I also have tattoos..back of my head, wrist, full back and anklet. All self-designed, all tribal, most significant. One is just a tat...a cool design. I'm also not a youth, or a criminal...or in the service. In fact, I see more older people with ink done now than I do younger....yes, the 50-60-somethings still hold fast to archaic veiws on how only rabble-rousers, punks and criminals have tats, but so be it. My tats have never cost me or prevented me from getting any job that I wanted. <br>
<br>
Many many cultures have been doing these (tats/piercings) things for thousands of years. If someone doesn't like me because I have those things, than so be it. I don't need to or have to deal with someone with some misguided morality, someone that will judge me on a first glance at all. It is, however, a shame that others will feel hurt or be outcasts by a few pretentious, arrogant uptight members of society. <p><Font color="#FF0033" link="#FF0033" vlink="#FF0033" alink="#000066"> 


