A difference can say as much about two people as a similiarity. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
No, people are not blank slates. But I veiw them as such when I first meet them. You'll be a loney loney person if you pre-judge everyone for superficial things (get off the smoking please, this isn't limited to that), and look for hidden agendas....<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I never once said anything about a hidden agendas. Where did you get that from? Just because someone has a tatoo, does't mean I can decipher some &quot;hidden agenda&quot; about them. I really don't care about people's agendas.<br>
<br>
<br>
