<br>
<br>
<br>
Really, I think you just liked to read more into my statements than what I was trying to say. Maybe you needed someone to fight with today. Maybe you just didn't like me attacking smokers. I dunno. <br>
<br>
I know this much: I don't believe in the mantra of &quot;don't judge a book by it's cover&quot;. Because to me, the cover *is* part of the book. It is only one part, and I give it what I feel is the proper weight in the final analysis, but I don't ignore it either. <br>
<br>
Everything about a person makes them who they are. To ignore any part of it is to ignore some part of that person. Would you want someone to ignore you? Even the smallest part of you? <br>
<br>
I try not to ignore anything about people. If that means I see the bad with the good, so be it. What matters is: can I overlook the bad, and focus on the good? And will that person do the same? <br>
<br>
<br>
-Krazak<br>
